or the\nNACO instrument, that can be used to predict the background level for bright\nstar observations. Conclusions: According to recent numerical models, the\nlimiting magnitude of our search sets the maximum mass of possible companions\nto 20-30 times Jupiter, between 7 and 20 AU from Alpha Cen B.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 24 Aug 2006 08:14:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-15"}
