nCold Dark Matter model, we compute the cosmic SFR per unit baryon mass in dark\nhaloes, i.e., the specific SFR. The specific SFR is found to scale with\nredshift as (1+z)^3 up to z~4, implying that the efficiency of star formation\nis on average higher at higher redshift in proportion to the cooling rate\nwithin dark haloes, while this is not simply the case at z>4.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 24 Aug 2006 09:53:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-26"}
